<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.4.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><updated>2026-05-03T23:24:29+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/feed.xml</id><title type="html">FEBQI</title><entry><title type="html">Welcome back, Xianjing!</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/xianjing-visit/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Welcome back, Xianjing!"/><published>2026-04-20T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-04-20T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/xianjing-visit</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/xianjing-visit/"><![CDATA[<p>Xianjing is visiting us for one week starting today.</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/lab-hp/assets/img/xianjing_visit_2026-480.webp 480w,/lab-hp/assets/img/xianjing_visit_2026-800.webp 800w,/lab-hp/assets/img/xianjing_visit_2026-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/lab-hp/assets/img/xianjing_visit_2026.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> <figcaption class="caption">Clockwise from left: Hochan, Takuma, Oleksiy, Jun, Ash, Yiran, Xianjing, Erika (Ivan on camera)</figcaption> </figure>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="visit"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Xianjing Zhou is visiting for one week]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Hochan Chung receives Best Bachelor’s Thesis Award</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/hochan-award/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hochan Chung receives Best Bachelor’s Thesis Award"/><published>2026-03-25T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-25T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/hochan-award</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/hochan-award/"><![CDATA[<p>Hochan Chung (Research Trainee) has received the Best Bachelor’s Thesis Award. Congratulations, Hochan!</p> <p><img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEh6uFVcUVnrVxX-29Ky0rdKEePieCmJMU_c5RJO5yXpRTWsEMJOUox1zs5SPDcPqP1HtRqRlSMedkAphWdosBjweYdRiP59J7-n9dsGGHIRggpzaZDvGB6DcLZoi9B0wxF_9Q_qzt-Ot5df9WVIIiagxsqPkwH5H6zBW-gn1zxpnpJkUxbd8GRhEIIbhNyM" alt="Hochan award"/></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="award"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Hochan Chung receives Best Bachelor's Thesis Award]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Happy 80th birthday, Oleksiy!</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/birthdays/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Happy 80th birthday, Oleksiy!"/><published>2026-03-10T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-03-10T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/birthdays</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/birthdays/"><![CDATA[<p>Oleksiy turned 80 (and Erika half that)! Happy birthday to both!</p> <p><img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEj9OueJAp3siWIZLxym-Unn1V-djB60k74J2o40JhkW-aBDARdlaIZILHnG2U5E0vIUjOrWIiMFlJTpuVsfJ1lHkFPF6eeaA2k7k136aGLg1oehMtOQ33E5UcioAD_3Ac-wNPa5RuJbM42Bz9WYbY_z7tKJKVF09Ewluenc7BY5cGRdzfJXyWOlpcTLrZlL/s320/BD.png" alt="Birthday"/></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="lab-life"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Celebrating birthdays in the lab]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Plasmon paper posted on arXiv</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/plasmon-arxiv/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Plasmon paper posted on arXiv"/><published>2026-01-29T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-01-29T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/plasmon-arxiv</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/plasmon-arxiv/"><![CDATA[<p>Our plasmon paper is now on arXiv! New results on collective excitations (plasmon modes) of electrons floating on liquid helium.</p> <p><strong>Strong Coupling Between RF Photons and Plasmons of Electrons on Liquid Helium</strong> Asher Jennings*, Ivan Grytsenko, Thomas Giovansili, Itay Josef Barabash, Oleksiy Rybalko, Yiran Tian, Jun Wang, Hiroki Ikegami, and Erika Kawakami* <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.22552">arXiv:2601.22552</a> (2026)</p> <p><img src="/lab-hp/assets/img/plasmon.png" alt="plasmon paper figure"/></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="publication"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Our plasmon paper is now on arXiv]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Our Review Article on Quantum Computing Published in a French Alumni Magazine</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/french-review-article/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Our Review Article on Quantum Computing Published in a French Alumni Magazine"/><published>2026-01-21T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-01-21T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/french-review-article</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2026/french-review-article/"><![CDATA[<p>A review article on quantum computing by Tetsuyoshi Yamada, Thomas Giovansili, and Erika Kawakami has been published in a French alumni magazine. Great outreach work!</p> <p><strong><a href="https://www.centraliens-mediterranee.fr/medias/editor/Cahiers-AIECM/N°59%20-%20Le%20Quantique/Sommaire%2059%20Le%20quantique.pdf">L’ordinateur quantique : promesses, défis et nouvelles pistes de recherche</a></strong> Tetsuyoshi Yamada, Thomas Giovansili, Erika Kawakami* <em>Les Cahiers de Centrale Méditerranée Alumni « Le quantique », N°59 (2025)</em> [<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/11JRIr3OF6UR6TVErzIOnd0asYnYGA6s1/edit?usp=sharing&amp;ouid=118183936351125371152&amp;rtpof=true&amp;sd=true">Draft</a>]</p> <p><img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEiuEfwxwy-viuGSJzS-RMvRhtKVNJyUHq3-MU5BGHXZ-82Oi8IinOAzcoafmJXfVdzh4jnpNSAK1LZSB9mJ3Pk4ta4Y_3vomPeRFMvzXveMZsso5HPl8PRooSg2nuUB9aqbQgsLikKP-FyQ-PineW5ydyfwqhvycOnCXBZp_r73qI3eRR7U67bw5DbE5Glp" alt="French article"/></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="publication"/><category term="outreach"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Review article by Yamada, Giovansili, and Kawakami published in French alumni magazine]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Tetsu’s farewell party</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2025/tetsu-farewell/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tetsu’s farewell party"/><published>2025-09-15T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-09-15T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2025/tetsu-farewell</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2025/tetsu-farewell/"><![CDATA[<p>We held a farewell party for Tetsuyoshi Yamada. Thank you, Tetsu, for your contributions to the team!</p> <p><img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEhHyhAJHoDQ_ekjfv7LYr9FcNL_eFExvNH5r73sSVgTlbh5s2m4T3NhMby5jGyhpLbiF9QVbk7FuHcnhvsQgZYc3wRcIgrBrMQo_GnTsC3FL6ryR45bgDz4HqkCbKnkg-5HNVgx6FxGdvm6QTTKQdOpsyVPHKl8yrLWwJnm5AtjxDrPLmT9jrYOnjKw9P2P" alt="Tetsu farewell"/></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="lab-life"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Farewell party for Tetsuyoshi Yamada]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Great News to Share</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2025/prl-editors-suggestion/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Great News to Share"/><published>2025-08-24T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-08-24T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2025/prl-editors-suggestion</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2025/prl-editors-suggestion/"><![CDATA[<p>Our Rydberg detection paper has been published in PRL and selected as an <strong>Editors’ Suggestion</strong>! Additionally, Ash received a poster award at the LT30 conference. Congratulations!</p> <p><strong><a href="https://link.aps.org/doi/10.1103/5y8p-qhb4">Probing the Quantum Capacitance of Rydberg Transitions of Surface Electrons on Liquid Helium via Microwave Frequency Modulation</a></strong> <u>Asher Jennings</u>*, <u>Ivan Grytsenko</u>, <u>Yiran Tian</u>, <u>Oleksiy Rybalko</u>, Jun Wang, Itay Josef Barabash, and <u>Erika Kawakami</u>* <em>Phys. Rev. Lett. 135, 087001 (2025)</em></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="publication"/><category term="award"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[PRL paper selected as Editors' Suggestion and poster award at LT30]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">New cryogenic microwave source developed using a tunnel diode oscillator</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/tdo-paper/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="New cryogenic microwave source developed using a tunnel diode oscillator"/><published>2024-12-12T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-12-12T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/tdo-paper</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/tdo-paper/"><![CDATA[<p>New cryogenic microwave source developed using a tunnel diode oscillator — achieving superior amplitude stability compared to commercial sources.</p> <p><strong><a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10909-025-03293-4">Characterization of Tunnel Diode Oscillator for Qubit Readout Applications</a></strong> <u>Ivan Grytsenko</u>, Sander van Haagen, <u>Oleksiy Rybalko</u>, <u>Asher Jennings</u>, <u>Rajesh Mohan</u>, <u>Yiran Tian</u>, and <u>Erika Kawakami</u>* <em>J. Low Temp. Phys. 219, 282 (2025)</em></p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="publication"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[New cryogenic microwave source developed using a tunnel diode oscillator]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Sander’s Farewell party</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/sander-farewell/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sander’s Farewell party"/><published>2024-08-01T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-08-01T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/sander-farewell</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/sander-farewell/"><![CDATA[<p>Thank you for your contribution to TDO, Sander! We wish you all the best!</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/lab-hp/assets/img/sander_farewell-480.webp 480w,/lab-hp/assets/img/sander_farewell-800.webp 800w,/lab-hp/assets/img/sander_farewell-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/lab-hp/assets/img/sander_farewell.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="80%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="lab-life"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Farewell party for Sander van Haagen]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">FCP workshop at OIST</title><link href="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/fcp-workshop-oist/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="FCP workshop at OIST"/><published>2024-06-06T15:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-06-06T15:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/fcp-workshop-oist</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://febqi.github.io/lab-hp/blog/2024/fcp-workshop-oist/"><![CDATA[<p>We all presented posters and gave talks. We thank Denis and OIST for organizing such a wonderful workshop!</p> <p><strong><a href="https://groups.oist.jp/fcp">OIST Workshop “Quantum Technologies with Floating Charged Particles”</a></strong></p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/lab-hp/assets/img/fcp_workshop-480.webp 480w,/lab-hp/assets/img/fcp_workshop-800.webp 800w,/lab-hp/assets/img/fcp_workshop-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/lab-hp/assets/img/fcp_workshop.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="90%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="news"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[OIST Workshop "Quantum Technologies with Floating Charged Particles"]]></summary></entry></feed>